Package JavaHw_2

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Employee
    Interface that works with person to add employee money and id methods
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Building
    Building base class, has a list of occupants, a name and an address building address allowed to change in case of street name change occupants of a building are there until removed; occupancy based on working/going to school in the building.
    City
    Represents a basic city and citizens Will at least have a city hall and one school City is created ground up by adding in more citizens and buildings after city hall and initial school
    CityHall
    extension of building,has a list of occupants, a name and an address; mostly has police occupants
    Kid
    Kid represents someone under 18: their favorite candy, name, age, phoneNumber, and the total amount of money they have
    Main
    contains all code and assertions used to test the classes in the package
    Person
    represents a basic person of any age, their name, age, phoneNumber, and the total amount of money they have no way to change age once set, since people are represented as static in time and as permanently occupying buildings (for clarity) all persons have a total amount of money
    Police
    Police represents someone over 18: their police role, ID, name, age, phoneNumber, and the total amount of money they have
    School
    extension of building, has a list of occupants, a name and an address; mainly has teacher and student occupants
    Teacher
    Teacher represents someone over 18: the grade level they can teach, the teaching certification degree they have, name, age, phoneNumber, and the total amount of money they have
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Police.Role
    enum of roles a police officer can have, akin to ranking
    Teacher.GradeLevel
    what grade level a teacher is certified to teach
    Teacher.TeachingCertification
    what certification the teacher has to teach
